cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on resource management in mobile edge computing systems, which involves wireless communication and networking. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with offloading computation from mobile devices to a proximate MEC server, which involves distributed computing. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes an algorithm for joint radio and computational resource management, which involves control theory. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses the Gauss-Seidel method to determine optimal transmit power and bandwidth allocation, which involves information theory. 
5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper discusses the optimal CPU-cycle frequencies of mobile devices and the MEC server, which involves hardware architecture.
